{
  "stem": "9943.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And now, the trip from Butovo.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In the meantime, in that Butovo-- and I have here those postcards.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In the meantime, I found a cousin-- my husband's cousin, the second daughter of that woman that is there with my relatives, with my in-laws.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And here the-- that I-- I found there Tamarovka [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Well, anyway, so I got her address in Syzran, and I got to them after a long travel.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The whole travel, I'm not going to go into it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I got to Syzran, which I joined that cousin-- my husband's cousin, [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Zonia's ?] cousin.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there, I got a better job.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "She didn't want me to get a job because her husband-- she preferred if I stay home with her.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They lived-- they left from Moscow to Syzran, he in connection with his work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "From there, I went with them, again, with the permission of the authorities, which I have here the documentation, went to Ufa.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And from Ufa, in November, I set out to go to Uzbekistan.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The reason I wanted to go to Uzbekistan-- Uzbekistan is close to-- to Iran and possibility to get out of-- of the Soviet Union and besides, to get somewhere where it's warm, because I didn't have any warm clothing, and it was early winter.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was already a long time winter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] I'm not going to go into that, because we don't have time for this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Briefly, I arrived to Uzbekistan.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It means that I arrived to Tashkent.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Tashkent is the capital of Uzbekistan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Tashkent, near the train, there were an awful lot of people from different places.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "At that time, they were talking about the Soviet Union as Russia on wheels.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And you didn't have a right to stay in Tashkent, so you couldn't.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
